The paper presents a data structure for maintaining a dynamic set of elements drawn from a partially ordered universe described by a tree. This problem falls under the category of data structures and algorithms, which is covered by cs.DS. The paper also discusses the width of the partial order, which is a measure of the complexity of the search problem. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of discrete mathematics (cs.DM), distributed computing (cs.DC), computational complexity (cs.CC), and machine learning (cs.LG).
